===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In oracle bone script, {{Han compound|ls=ic|衣|又|t1=clothes|t2=hand|nocap=yes}} – "to put on clothes; to wear", representing the original form of {{och-l|擐|id=2}} ({{zh-ref|Qiu, 1985}}, {{zh-ref|Chi, 2014}}). Some variant forms added 〇 (the earliest form of {{och-l|圓|circle}}, now written {{zh-l|*口}}) as a sound component. The component {{zh-l|*又}} has corrupted into {{zh-l|*㞢}} in seal script and {{zh-l|*土}} in clerical script.

